RESOLUTION CONCERNING THE REAUTHORIZATION OF THE
COMMUNITY INVESTMENT FUND BOARD AND PROGRAM.
Resolved by this Assembly:
1 WHEREAS, the Community Investment Fund 2030 Board was
2 established pursuant to section 32-285a of the general statutes to carry
3 out certain duties, including, but not limited to, reviewing applications
4 for funds from bonds of the state for certain eligible projects and
5 submitting to the Governor a list of eligible projects that the board
6 recommends be funded;
7 WHEREAS, subsection (e) of section 32-285a of the general statutes
8 requires that the General Assembly affirm by resolution the
9 reauthorization of the Community Investment Fund 2030 Board and the
10 program provided for under such section prior to the State Bond
11 Commission authorizing the issuance of bonds for the purpose of
12 funding eligible projects for the fiscal years ending June 30, 2028, to June
13 30, 2032, inclusive; and
14 WHEREAS, it is in the best interest of the state to reauthorize the
15 Community Investment Fund 2030 Board and the program provided for
LCO No. 525 1 of 2

House Joint Resolution No. 31
16 under section 32-285a of the general statutes;
17 NOW, THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED, that the Community
18 Investment Fund 2030 Board and the program provided for under
19 section 32-285a of the general statutes is reauthorized.
LCO No. 525 2 of 2

